  "texts": [
    "Indeed, F1 scores and support (number of labels in the evaluation set) are highly correlated, with Pearson correlation of 0.84 and 0.82 for all categories in the development and test sets, respectively.",
    "When taking the imbalanced sample into account, model performance is even more encouraging.",
    "For example, tactics has a seemingly low F1-score of 0.594, but a random baseline classifier by comparison has in expectation an F1-score of just 0.191.",
    "Nevertheless, we decide to exclude stance and framing categories with F1-scores below 0.5 from further analysis in order to increase the reliability of our analysis.",
    "We thus omit the lowest performing frame element, counterframing."
  ],
